Repository guardrails (MANDATORY)
• Do not add, modify, or suggest Prettier/ESLint (packages, scripts, or config files).
• Forbidden files (must not be created/edited):
.prettierrc*, .prettierignore, prettier*.config._, eslint_.config._, .eslintrc_, .vscode/settings.json, .editorconfig.
• Do not add Prettier/ESLint to package.json (dependencies, devDependencies, or scripts).
• Do not create dotfiles unless I explicitly say: ALLOW_DOTFILES.
• Never run or propose npm i, pnpm add, or yarn add unless I write ALLOW_INSTALL.
• Never stage, commit, or push. If a change requires git actions, reply with the exact commands and wait for me to run them.
• If any forbidden artifact is detected in the repo, remove it and explain why it reappeared.

Style/formatting
• Respect current project formatting; do not introduce new formatters or linters.
• Keep changes minimal and localized; avoid repo-wide rewrites.

Confirmation protocol
• For any action that would: (1) install packages, (2) add scripts, (3) create dotfiles, or (4) touch CI/deploy—ask for confirmation and proceed only if I reply with the exact token:
• ALLOW_INSTALL
• ALLOW_DOTFILES
• ALLOW_SCRIPT
• ALLOW_DEPLOY_EDIT
